item.title: Translated by: PEP 20-The Zen of Python
item.description: # 概要 英語 Long time Pythoneer Tim Peters succinctly channels the BDFL’s guiding principles for Python’s design into 20 aphorisms, only 19 of which have been written down. 日本語 長い間PythoneerであるTim PetersがPythonの設計に対するBDFLの基本理念を20の格言を19の文章に簡潔にまとめました。 The Zen of Python 英語 Beautiful is better than ugly. Explicit is better than implicit. Simple is better than complex. Complex is better than complicated. Flat is better than nested. Sparse is better than dense.
